Subtitle of Senate Bill 303
TO ALLOW A RESIDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT TO PERMIT A PRIVATE SCHOOL
STUDENT TO PARTICIPATE IN AN INTERSCHOLASTIC ACTIVITY AT THE RESIDENT
SCHOOL DISTRICT UNDER CERTAIN CONDITIONS.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 2 to Senate Bill 303
Amend Senate Bill 303 as originally introduced:
Page 2, delete lines 13 and 14, and substitute the following:
"(5) "Resident school" means:
(A) A public school to which a student would be assigned
by the student's resident school district; or
(B) An open-enrollment public charter school with a campus
located within the student's resident school district; and"
AND
Page 2, line 18, delete "district may" and substitute "district or an open-
enrollment public charter school may"
AND
Page 2, line 20, delete "district if the" and substitute "if the"
